6.2. Permutation test - Checking observed vs expected values

Lorenzo Bertola

Document last run on 2024-07-02

  • 0. Load packages and input data
  • 1. Observed sex-linked markers
    • 1.1 Observed sex-linked markers by scaffold
  • 2. Expected sex-linked markers
  • 3. Plot results
  • 4. Summarise results by lineage
  • 5. Plot results by scaffold

Now we will assess whether the number of sex-linked markers is significantly more than expected by chance, by comparing the observed number to the expected distribution derived from the permutations.

1. Observed sex-linked markers

Let's calculate how many XY and how many ZW were found for each method for each pop.

counts <- my.df %>% group_by(Pop, Method, SexDet) %>%
  summarise(sexlinked = table(SexDet))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Pop', 'Method'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
AllCombs <- expand_grid(Pop = c("P1","P2","P3","P4","P5","P6","P7",
                                "P8","P9","P10","P11","P12","P13",
                                "P14","P15"),
                        Method = c("Method1","Method2","Method3",
                                   "Method4","Method5"),
                        SexDet = c("XY","ZW"))

counts <- left_join(AllCombs, counts) %>%
  mutate(sexlinked = case_when(is.na(sexlinked) == TRUE ~ as.integer(0),
                       TRUE ~ as.integer(sexlinked) ))
## Joining with `by = join_by(Pop, Method, SexDet)`

Let's visualise it

ggplot(counts) +

  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))

2. Expected sex-linked markers

Now we want to calculate how many sex-linked markers were obtained on average for each method during permutations.

XY <- my.perms %>%
  filter(SexDet=="XY") %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method) %>%
  count(PermID)

ZW <- my.perms %>%
  filter(SexDet=="ZW") %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method) %>%
  count(PermID)

Add rows with 0 for permutations that found no sex-linked markers

Pop <- c("P1","P2","P3","P4","P5","P6","P7","P8","P9","P10","P11","P12","P13","P14","P15")
Method <- c("Method1","Method2","Method3","Method4","Method5")
PermID <- seq(1,10000,1)

AllCombs <- expand_grid(Pop,Method,PermID)

XY <- left_join(AllCombs,XY) %>% mutate(n = case_when(is.na(n) == TRUE ~ as.integer(0),
                                                      TRUE ~ as.integer(n) ))
## Joining with `by = join_by(Pop, Method, PermID)`
ZW <- left_join(AllCombs,ZW) %>% mutate(n = case_when(is.na(n) == TRUE ~ as.integer(0),
                                                      TRUE ~ as.integer(n) ))
## Joining with `by = join_by(Pop, Method, PermID)`
rm(Pop,Method,PermID,AllCombs)

Keep current format for plotting violin plots later

XY.1 <- XY %>% add_column("SexDet"="XY")
ZW.1 <- ZW %>% add_column("SexDet"="ZW")

XYZW <- rbind(XY.1, ZW.1)

rm(XY.1, ZW.1)

Calculate mean and quantiles per pop per method.

XY <- XY %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method) %>%
  summarise(quant95 = quantile(n,0.95),
            quant99 = quantile(n,0.99),
            average = mean(n)) %>%
  add_column("SexDet"="XY")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Pop'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
ZW <- ZW %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method) %>%
  summarise(quant95 = quantile(n,0.95),
            quant99 = quantile(n,0.99),
            average = mean(n)) %>%
  add_column("SexDet"="ZW")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Pop'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
perm.counts <- rbind(XY,ZW)

rm(XY,ZW)

Now merge with observed values

counts <- left_join(counts,perm.counts)
## Joining with `by = join_by(Pop, Method, SexDet)`

Add column with significance

counts <- counts %>%
  mutate(significance = case_when(sexlinked > quant99 ~ "**",
                                      sexlinked > quant95 ~ "*",
                                      sexlinked > average ~ "above.average",
                                      TRUE ~ "NS"))

my.plots <- mapply(function(x,y){

                  size=1.5,

               size=3, position=position_dodge(width = 0.5)) +

5. Plot results by scaffold

Now, let's assess co-localisation of markers from groups of markers (i.e., same Method, same SexDet, same species) that comprise significantly more markers than expected by chance.

rm(my.counts, my.plots, plot.all, perm.counts, my.pops)

Retain only markers identified from methods that returned more sex-linked markers than expected by chance (at q 0.99)

sig.methods <- counts %>%
  filter(significance=="**") %>%
  mutate(SigID = paste(Pop,Method,SexDet,sep = "_")) %>%
  pull(SigID)

my.sig <- my.df %>%
  mutate(SigID = paste(Pop,Method,SexDet,sep = "_")) %>%
  filter(SigID %in% sig.methods)

Count markers per scaffold, grouping by population, method and sex determination system

SLbyScaf <- my.sig %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method, SexDet,Scaffold) %>%
  summarise(nSexLinked = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Pop', 'Method', 'SexDet'. You can override
## using the `.groups` argument.

Calculate expected number of markers per scaffold from permutations

SLbyScaf_perm <- my.perms %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method, SexDet,Scaffold,PermID) %>%
  summarise(SLbyScaf = n()) %>%
  filter(SLbyScaf > 1)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Pop', 'Method', 'SexDet', 'Scaffold'. You
## can override using the `.groups` argument.
SLbyScaf_perm <- SLbyScaf_perm %>%
  group_by(Pop, Method, SexDet,Scaffold) %>%
  summarise(meanByScaf = mean(SLbyScaf),
            p95 = quantile(SLbyScaf, 0.95),
            p99 = quantile(SLbyScaf, 0.99)) %>%
  mutate(Scaffold = as.integer(Scaffold))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Pop', 'Method', 'SexDet'. You can override
## using the `.groups` argument.

Create list of all possible combinations

AllCombs <- expand_grid(Pop = unique(my.df$Pop),
                        Method = unique(my.df$Method),
                        SexDet = c("XY","ZW"),
                        Scaffold = as.double(unique(SLbyScaf_perm %>%
                                                       ungroup() %>% pull(Scaffold))))

Join observed and expected into one table

SLbyScaf <- left_join(AllCombs, SLbyScaf %>% ungroup)
## Joining with `by = join_by(Pop, Method, SexDet, Scaffold)`
SLbyScaf <- left_join(SLbyScaf, SLbyScaf_perm)
## Joining with `by = join_by(Pop, Method, SexDet, Scaffold)`
SLbyScaf <- SLbyScaf %>% filter(is.na(nSexLinked)==FALSE) %>%
  mutate(meanByScaf = case_when(is.na(meanByScaf)==TRUE~0,
                                TRUE ~ meanByScaf),
         p95 = case_when(is.na(p95)==TRUE~0,
                                TRUE ~ p95),
         p99 = case_when(is.na(p99)==TRUE~0,
                                TRUE ~ p99)) %>%
  filter(Scaffold<14)
#we only detected one marker in scaffolds above 13, so we removed it

Identify significant ones

SLbyScaf <- SLbyScaf %>%
  mutate(signif = case_when(nSexLinked > p99 ~ "**",
                            nSexLinked > p95 ~ "*",
                            TRUE ~ "ns"),
         SigID = paste(Pop,Method,SexDet, sep = "_"))

Save Table S8

write_csv(SLbyScaf, file = "../6_Permutations/6_4_SignificanceTableByScaffold.csv")

Plot

sig.text.99 <- SLbyScaf %>% filter(signif == "**")
#sig.text.95 <- SLbyScaf %>% filter(signif == "*")

p1 <- ggplot(SLbyScaf) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(x=Method,
                    ymax=p99, ymin=0, colour=SexDet),
                  alpha = 1/3, position=position_dodge(width = 0.5)) +
  geom_point(aes(x=Method,y=meanByScaf,fill=SexDet),
               colour="black", alpha = 1/3, size=3,
               position=position_dodge(width = 0.5)) +
  geom_point(aes(x=Method, y=nSexLinked, fill=SexDet, colour=SexDet)) +
  geom_text(data=sig.text.99, aes(x=Method, y=28),label="**") +
  #geom_text(data=sig.text.95, aes(x=Method, y=20),label="*") +
  theme_classic() +
  ylab("Number of sex-linked markers identified") +
  facet_grid(Scaffold~Pop) +

  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0,10,20,30), limits = c(0,30))
